Hey! It’s Libby, Ginnie, and Jessica, three gardeners / illustrators / friends. We’ve been quietly working away to bring you our first issue of The Garden People: a biannual zine about gardens and their people! Inside you'll find illustrations, short essays, and poetry inspired by our affinity for all things leafy, petaled, wild and rooted. Stay tuned for more details about when and where to purchase a copy 😊🌻🦋🐛! #thegardenpeople

Cover reveal! 🌱 We (@ginniehsu , @jessicasroux , and myself) are so excited to share the cover of our first issue of The Garden People, a biannual zine all about gardens and their people, featuring illustration by the incredible @ginniehsu! Here she perfectly captures the feeling of joy a summer garden brings. This issue's theme is BEGINNINGS, and is filled with illustrations and short essays from the three of us. We hope you enjoy it as much as we we did making it! 💚🌼

You can order through our individual shops now. See you in the garden!

In this first issue of The Garden People, I chose to write about my less-than-perfect compost journey for the theme of BEGINNINGS. Afterall, gardening is as much about the soil as it is about the pretty and tasty stuff growing on top of it! I had simple goals-- divert kitchen scraps from the waste stream and create supercharged soil. Things did not go *exactly* as planned 😬, but spoiler alert: I created my beautiful compost in the end! 🌱

Click the link in bio to purchase our summer issue of The Garden People ☺️🐛🌼, filled with short essays and illustrations by myself, @ginniehsu , and @jessicasroux

Happy gardening!

#thegardenpeople

Wow wow wow, or maybe bow wow wow is more like it?!! Heading to Brooklyn next weekend for @greenpointers + @dustyrosevintage 's @openairfair to do LIVE pet portraits and I hope to see you and maybe your pup there (if they do well in crowds of course 😉)! And if you don't already have a pup, well you are in luck my friend because this is a very special episode of Open Air Fair, featuring adoptions by Muddy Paws, Waldo, & Rescue City! Really hope to see you there! I mean, is there any better way to spend a weekend than with a bunch of dogs, yummy snacks, and vintage shopping?

Greenpointers was pretty much where I launched my illustration career about a decade ago, so it's extra special to me to get to reunite this way! I used to have my own critter-centric illustrated recipe column on their blog called "Recipes Gone Wild", which I printed up as cookbook zines 💕, and I also created hand-painted photo backdrops for their seasonal markets. And that's where I met Maresa of Dusty Rose, one of the most amazing people I know and get to call a dear friend. Was so psyched she invited me to be a part of this weekend's fair 🐕🐾 because I'm a crazy dog lady now and she fully supports!! 

So come by, say hi! Get a portait, get a dog, get both, or just come make a pup's day more special with some love and attention. They deserve to be seen and loved.

Cheers!

#openairair #greenpointers #dustyrosevintage #adoptdontshop

Especially not pleased to hear I was hanging out with literally 50 other dogs 🤪❤️

Woohoo! Happy opening day to @levainbakery's new Chicago River North location!! 🍾🍪💙 Just love Chicago and loved illustrating the neighborhood for you :) 

Fun fact: when I lived in Chicago, my first job there was at the old Pearl Paint at the Chicago Ave brown line stop in River North! What a fun job. One day Ozzy Osbourne wandered in with two bodyguards while taking a break from Ozzfest to buy markers and pens. He loved doodling while on tour 💙 He was an absolute dear! Later that day he sent us a bunch of tickets to the festival ⚡⚡! Not cookie related, but still sweet 😉

#levainbakery #chicagorivernorth #givemeallthecookies
